description: Former bad guy Lincoln Stanley, aka Hep Cat, wants to take up where he left off with Judo Girl back in the swinging 60s, but Diana begins to have second thoughts about his motives. And sexy assassin Silencer's new modus operandi seems to be all over the map - what is she up to, and why?

Silencer never misses...so why did she let her newest victim live? Judo Girl uncovers the reasons why. And Lincoln (a.k.a. Hep Cat) has been drugging and manipulating Diana to further his own agenda. It's all perfectly logical, according to Lincoln, but Judo Girl is not amused, and not even Atlas can calm her down.

Judo Girl knows Lincoln (a.k.a. Hep Cat) is somehow behind her recent blackouts and she storms his Malibu mansion in search of the truth. But Lincoln anticipates her coming and prepares for their final confrontation. Not only does Judo Girl discover the final fate of the assassin Silencer, she will bring Lincoln to justice - even if it means sacrificing her secret identity.

Trapped on the island with her crew, cornered by a vengeful sea god, Hanna will have to use all of her wits to escape! Add to this Captain Purloin has finally caught up with her. Can she survive what is about to come down upon her? Was her trusting of the young island survivor Robbie Buckle her undoing, even if it had led her to more treasure than she had ever seen?
name: Issue 4

description: From the accounts of the First Book of Samuel, this story begins the retelling of the most powerful General of Israel. Anointed as a young boy and mocked by his brothers and family, young David is even hunted by the king himself. While hiding in a wilderness cave, David looks back on the fateful day he was anointed by a prophet, realizing he's been fighting a battle even from his youth in his father's sheepfold.
name: Issue 1

description: The dark words of a prophecy hang over the head of the king of Israel, while Samuel the prophet searches for a new king and the young shepherd David places himself between his flock and the jaws of a hungry lion.

According to the prophesy of Samuel, David has become the annointed heir to the throne of Israel. According to his brothers, David has become a laughing stock. Has Samuel gone mad? Does Davis destiny truely lie in Jeruselem, as king of a nation, or in the fields, as shepherd to his father's flock? Don't miss the conclusion to this epic story as young David confronts the jeers of his brothers, and King Saul confonts the spirit of his demise.

Deal with the Devil is the tale of a man who once had it all; family, faith, health, the respect and adoration of his peers, and the reputation as the best homicide detective in FBI history. In his last case, his prey became his hunter, and his career was ended in shame and worthlessness. Four years later, his nemesis returns to ask for... his help. Find out why in this thrilling journey through the darkness in a world where things are never what they seem...
name: The Devil You Know

description: What does it take for a man to agree to help someone who took his leg, his faith, and his purpose for living? Meet former FBI agent Anthony Goodwin and the serial killer who ruined his life, Kevin Runyan, as the two strike a deal to save the life of an innocent girl. This issue: A bargain is struck between enemies to save Kevin's sister, Katrina. The hunt is on and the clock is ticking as Anthony tries to become again what he once was, the best detective in FBI history.
name: The Devil Take You

description: Agent Goodwin starts piecing things together, when the kidnapper interrupts his investigation, and the chase begins! Motivations are revealed, and preconceptions are shattered as we learn the 'truth' behind the Red Letter Killings. Don't miss this pivotal issue of what some are calling the best crime noir since Frank Miller's Sin City!

The clock is ticking and the puzzle pieces seem to be falling into place as Agent Goodwin pinpoints his suspect. The only problem now is that Kevin has been sent off to commit one last Red Letter Killing in order to save the life of his sister.
name: What the Devil Knows

description: The conclusive issue! Time is up, and an innocent is about to die, unless Anthony's guess is right and he can get there in time to stop Kevin from making one last Red Letter Killing! But things aren't quite what they seem as the truth begins to unravel!
name: The Devil's Due

description: A thousand years ago in ancient China the monks of Shang Ti Do kept safeguard over the prison of a thousand demons. But a young monk was fooled into releasing these demons, which in retribution laid waste to the monks and the Temple of God of China. Charged with the responsibility and the guilt of his action, the boy devoted his life and his family line to recapturing the demons. Now, a thousand years later, the last descendent of the Devil's Keepers must find a replacement!
name: Issue 1

description: After losing his son Jun to the fearsome demon known as Chi Tao, Devil Hunter Lee Chang has begun training three new potentials to preserve the teachings of the martial arts style known as Shang Ti Do.

Paul, Asher, and Tyrone are the star students of the Shang Ti Do Academy, but as they are tested by their aging instructor, Lee Chang, they are all found lacking as potential heirs to the seat of mastery. Can the power of Shang Ti Do help them to fuse together incredible feats of mind, soul and body?

Billy Andrews, a Hollywood stuntman who's struggling in his relationship with a rising film starlet, Laura Leigh, and to keep his fledgling stunt company, Killer Stunts, Inc., afloat in the new age of CGI-dominated special effects is sucked into an assignment from a covert government agency, not knowing he's being used as a pawn in a vast conspiracy. In over his head, the daredevil-for-hire re-teams with his former mentor, John Lynch, an aging legend in the stunt community, and is forced to utilize all his "tricks of the trade" to not only stay alive, but to stop the bad guys from pulling off a major heist.

Stuntman Billy Andrews finds himself staring down the gun of a mysterious foe whose been dogging his every step and sabotaging the sets of his films. To add insult to injury, this deadly individual appears to have been aided by Billy's own friend and mentor, one of the world's most legendary daredevils. Everywhere Billy turns, a new trap is sprung; even one by his own girlfriend. Can even Hollywood's top stuntman survive the pitfalls of both love and war?

The stunts are truly killer this issue, and someone is going to die! Stuntman Billy Andrews races to track down the kidnapper of his girl, Hollywood starlet Laura Leigh. But he hits a brick wall, hard, as someone he loves dies before his eyes. He's made a career out of cheating death, but now the reaper's icy grip is slowly closing in upon Billy and everyone around him. There's only one way out: go faster, fly higher, burn brighter, and hit harder than the bad guys.

Stuntman Billy Andrews is forced to recover quickly from the death of a friend, while Hollywood starlet Laura Leigh held at gunpoint by a turncoat government agent. Billy and his team are coerced into performing a dangerous aerial stunt in order to fake the death of a wealthy drug lord.

Alice, Jim Hawkins, The Pied Piper, Red Riding Hood, and Pinocchio. They are an unsual group of allies, forged into an alliance by a quest that leads them to the city of Oz. A quest that, if they fail, could spell disaster for the land of Lullaby. A quest that just may be cut short by the one called Makoma, "The Great One," a small fox with a knack for stealing the fairyland people's powers and abilities. And with Pinocchio already under his control, his sights are now set on the rest of the band.

The battle with Makoma almost over, Alice, Jim Hawkins, the Piper, and Red Riding Hood now face another betrayal... within their own ranks. Is the warrior woman known as Milady what she claims to be? The band of heroes has put their trust in her, but at what cost? And, weakened by battle and betrayal, can they stand in their first meeting with the fairy land's greatest evil, the one called Crow?

Alice (from Wonderland), the pirate Jim Hawkins, the famed Piper, Red Riding Hood, Pinocchio, Cheshire Cat, and the French swords-woman Milady must join forces against the fairy realm's greatest evil. But will their combined might be enough to vanquish his power? Meanwhile, the secrets behind Milady's swords, Makoma's bag, and the third little pig are all revealed.

Meet Marty and Alexis, two very different people that are forced to be together when they mysteriously gain super powers that only work when they are together! This fun, all ages comic is brought to you by former Disney animator Tom Bancroft.
name: First Issue

description: Ater a freak elevator accident, Marty and Alexis begin to manifest strange super powers. Marty, web designer and all around "geek," couldn't be more thrilled. Alexis, an upwardly mobile attorney, has quite the opposite feeling. But how did they get these powers, and why has Marty's dog, Bopper, suddenly expanded his vocabulary?

The further adventures of Marty and Alexis, two very different strangers who accidentally gain super powers. The rub is that the powers only work correctly when they are together! In this issue, the twosome discovers that their pets have also been mysteriously changed - one will become their new leader, the other, their first foe!

The exciting conclusion of the 4-part story arc of two very different people that accidentally gain superpowers and are forced to work together. In this issue, Marty and Alexis have a fight to the finish with the dog-monster Waggles, Canine of Fury!

The incredible series that was nominated for Eisner, Harvey, and Russ Manning Awards is now in never before seen full-color. This is the way Pakkins' Land was meant to be seen. A series of strange events brings Paul to a fantastic world called "Pakkins' Land." There he meets a mysterious giant Eagle of light who gives him a feather as a token of friendship. At the touch of this feather Paul feels something magical, and as the Eagle mysteriously vanishes, Paul realizes that he is lost in this new world. Soon Paul is befriended by a pair of extraordinary talking animals, who set off together to find the long lost King Aryah, and try to return Paul to his own land. The pathway is not without danger.
name: First Issue

description: The incredible series that was nominated for Eisner, Harvey, and Russ Manning Awards, is now in never-before-seen full-color! This is the way Pakkins' Land was meant to be seen! A series of strange events brings our hero, a boy named Paul, to a fantastic world called "Pakkins' Land." There he meets a mysterious giant Eagle of light, who gives him a feather as a token of friendship. At the touch of this feather, Paul feels something magical and realizes that there is something special about it. Paul is soon befriended by extraordinary talking animals, who join him in his dangerous quest to find their long lost King Aryah, and find a way for Paul to return to his own land.

The incredible series that was nominated for "Eisner" "Harvey" and "Russ Manning" Awards is now in never before seen full-color. A series of strange events brings a boy named Paul to a fantastic world where a mysterious giant Eagle of Light gives him a feather as a token of friendship. At the touch of this feather Paul feels something is magical about it. Soon he is befriended by extraordinary talking animals! Sure to appeal to all ages and fans who enjoy the works of C.S. Lewis, L. Frank Baum, J.R.R. Tolkien, and Jeff Smith.
Paul's pathway home is interrupted when he sent headlong over a great cliff...How can he ever survive? This wonderful series has been nominated for Eisner, Harvey, and Russ Manning Awards.

Paul's missing, so Mr. Brambles, Gus, and Shahni set out to retrieve him. As they make their way down "Death Ridge," Brambles tells of the great battle that took place on the very path they are travelling to find their friend. This delightful series that's nominated for Eisner, Harvey, and Russ Manning Awards, is now in full-color!

'Kung Fu' meets 'The Karate Kid' in this classic tale about a boy in search of his father.The teenaged Sixgun Samurai is on his way east to find his father, his last known living relative. But as he travels across the untamed prairie, he finds that dangerous men with dark motives are in pursuit, prepared to kill him to take his swords for reasons they dare not explain.

East meets West in this not to be missed in this action packed Wild West adventure!
name: Shot One: Frustration

description:
In the last days of the Wild West, the teenaged Sixgun Samurai is on his way east to find his father, his last known living relative. But as he travels across the untamed prairie, he finds himself tangled up with dangerous men and dark motives, forcing him to use his skills as a trick shooter and a swordsman to the utmost should he wish to survive.How could a boy living in the Wild West become a sharpshooting samurai?

As Sixgun Sam explains the origin of his unique abilities, he also reveals the nature of the tragedy that claimed the life of his mother ... and sent him on a voyage to St. Louis to track down a father he's never met. With its unique premise and high-caliber action, this second installment of Sixgun Samurai promises to enthrall readers looking for something different on comic book shelves.

In the tradition of Ferris Bueller's Day Off, Freaks & Geeks, and Sixteen Candles comes a new ongoing series from Alias - Super Teen*Topia! While 'A-list' teen super heroes travel to other dimensions and fight cosmic overlords, the STT gang gets stuck at the mall waiting for a bus! In this issue Paige, Cameron, and Kevin meet for the first time as they respond to a crisis with their untested powers. If you're ready for a comic series that focuses more on character than it does costume - Super Teen*Topia is the brand new 'super soap' in town!
name: First Issue

description: Everyone knows that top tier super-heroes, like the X-Men, relax after saving the galaxy by playing softball, but what do other groups do? Join the cast of Super Teen*Topia as they go miniature golfing! In this issue Kevin arranges a first date with his Internet girlfriend at the local miniature golf course. But when trouble rears it's head, will they be up to the task of saving the day? Plus, Paige makes a surprising revelation that will bring her one step closer to meeting Kevin face-to-face!

Being a teen super-hero means you always get picked first in PE, right? In this issue see why super-powers don't necessarily make you a star athlete as Cameron Smith takes on the girls volleyball team! Plus, Blackjack and Diva practice flying and discover it's best to look both ways before taking to the unfriendly skies. Don't miss the highly acclaimed super-soap that puts character before costume.

Keldegarde, a young Valkyrie, finds the heroic in the most unusual places. When she returns to Valhalla with her latest warrior, she unwittingly starts a chain of events that will change the face of Norse mythology forever. The adventure of a lifetime begins here!
name: First Issue

description: From actor/screenwriter and co-creator/star of Underworld, Kevin Grevioux! The story continues as Keldegarde learns exactly what it means to be a Valkyrie. Also, what is the trickster Loki up to? Find out in the second thrilling installment of Valkyries!

They say it takes a thief to catch a thief, and the glamorous field agents of Victoria's Secret Service put this tenant to the test when they allow their newest member, the American sneak-thief Scarlet, to take point on her first full mission. Hoping to derail an imminent coronation, it seems that an unknown scoundrel has stolen the Crown Jewels from the Tower of London! It's up to Lark, Raven, Brooke, and Scarlet to steal back these vibrant symbols of the monarchy they have sworn to protect. But which of her teammates is spying on Scarlet? And why? It's thief versus thief and spy versus spy in this high-impact thriller.

The beautiful-but-deadly 18-year-old twin sisters Bren and Bera have finished their training in the ways of war and have dedicated themselves to insuring the future peace of their homeland. But how can you establish peace in a country torn by war if you can't even get along with your own sister? Will they join forces in time to stand against the malevolent Warlord who is determined to take over their homeland, and possesses weapons that are not of this world?
name: First Issue

description: While in the camp of their enemy, Bren and Bera find weapons that are literally out of this world! The origin of the Killing Words weapons is also revealed. But will this vital information be discovered too late to warn their father and his forces? Sparks continue to fly between these two siblings as a fortress is besieged, a romance blossoms, and traitor is revealed!

Beaulie Betrayed by one of their own, Bren, Bera and their war party build an unlikely alliance with the strange but powerful people of the North. Meanwhile Braxon's siege of Thorfin castle climaxes in a battle between Skullsplitter and Braxon himself. The clash of the two warlords, and its outcome, will change the girls forever!

Eddie Ellison has just been violently thrust into the world of superheroes. Now called 'Silverwing,' he is teamed with a group of self-absorbed, childstar superheroes, who seek fame more than they seek justice. And they're not crazy about sharing the spotlight with a former 'pedestrian' either! Superhero action the way you like it!

name: Paperinik vice supereroe

volume.name: The Deadliest Heroes of Kung Fu

description:
Deathwind:

Story by Scott Newhouse

Pencils: Jason Brightman

Ink/Breakdowns/Letters: Loremzo Lizana

Boys Night Out:

Story: Scott Newhouse

Art: Jim Mahfood
name: Deathwind

description: Trip-trot, trip-trot? Will-O'-the-wisps? The king polishes his crown and tells his curious youngest daughter that he has arranged marriages between two of his daughters and two of the sons of the Goblin Chief of Norway. A special party is held and the two sons prove rough and rowdy. The elf maidens are presented as potential brides, proclaiming their most notable talents. The Goblin Chief is so delighted he chooses one for his wife. The two sons of the Goblin King hurry outside to continue their horseplay. Will the Goblin King's sons choose a bride? Will they blow out the will-o'-the-wisps? Beautifully illustrated, this comic graphic fairy tale captures the imagination of readers of all ages and inspires a love of reading.
name: The Elf Mound

description: A needle in a haystack? A goat in his pocket? A calf on his head? There once was a lad named William who was as silly as the day is long, everyone called him Silly Willy! Although Silly Willy tries to do what he is told he always gets mixed up, until the day his silliness leads him to find a bride. Will Silly Willy marry Gretel? Will Silly Willy and Gretel live happily ever after? Beautifully illustrated, this comic graphic fairy tale captures the imagination of readers of all ages and inspires a love of reading.
name: Silly Willy

description:
It's the end of Ellie's senior year, and as though final exams aren't enough to worry about, she's been placed in a compromising position by one of her bosses at a comic book company. Is quitting her only option?  

J.T turns to the Internet to help cope with the recent troubles in his life. But now he spends most of his ttime locked in his room, and he can't seem to move on. Is his new habit just making things worse?
name: Turning Japanese

description: Supergirl and Flamebird continue their slugfest, with poor Nightwing caught in the middle! Wait, isn't that man standing over there the same Reactron who murdered Supergirl's dad and Flamebird's surrogate father? Get him! Continued in SUPERGIRL #46... And in the new Captain Atom co-feature, the mystery of where (and when) Captain Atom is heats up when someone with a connection to Metropolis arrives on the scene. But are they friend or foe?
name: The Hunt for Reactron Part 3

description:
The shattering conclusion to 'The Depths' is here! The Six find themselves pitted against Artemis, Wonder Woman and the hideous secret being from deep within the new Devil's Island!

Grendel has found Wonder Woman bond up and ready for him but before he can devour her, he is interrupted by Mr. Smyth. Mr. Smyth would like Grendel to kill the other Amazons and the defective Secret Six who are currently in his prison.

Meanwhile, Catman, Jeannette and the Amazon are making their way to the roof. Bane, has found Scandal Savage, who has taken Bane's Venom herself. Deadshot and Ragdoll are tracking Catman to kill him, as per Mr. Smyth's orders.

Catman and Jeannette are attacked by Giuana, who confesses she is an Amazon too. They are saved by Deadshot who realizes friends are more important then money, this time. He shoots Giuana and Catman dismembers her, so she can't regenerate.

Scandal and Bane find Grendel, but are no match for him and Wonder Woman comes to their rescue.

Mr. Smyth plans on flooding the prison with gas, killing everyone but Ragdoll finds him and hits him in the head with a wrench.

When Artemis and the Amazons get to the roof they learn that if they go home the US government will attack Themyscira for them, so they decides the only way is suicide, but Wonder Woman stops them just in time. The Amazon agree to stay on Devil's Island under the watchful eye of each other and the warden. Wonder Woman then tell Scandal to get her team off the island or else.

On the helicopter Bane informs Scandal that he is now the leader of the team and his first order is she is off the team. Meanwhile, Deadshot has tracked down Mr. Smyth and kills him just like he killed Mina, back in issue #10
name: Depths Part Five: Early Release
Qui, Quo, Qua e le gioie del BMX
Qui, Quo, Qua e le gioie del BMX (p.2)

description: Join David and his mighty men in this whimsical but reverent retelling of some of the Bible's greatest heroes. Created by Marvel, DC, and Dark Horse Comics creator, Javier Saltares. Two complete stories in one 64-page graphic novel that includes "Trust: Four Against Four Hundred?" and "The Giant Mole Hill."

Topolino e la moneta di Creta
